  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will examine whether brain stimulation paired with social skills learning can
      help teenage boys with autism learn how to make and keep friends. Brain stimulation can
      enhance learning in some people. This study involves enrolling in a 14-week training program
      where teenage boys with autism interact in small groups and learn social skills. During the
      14-week program participants will receive active brain stimulation, or non-active
      stimulation (placebo). Before and after this training, MRI scans will be taken to see
      whether the training with active brain stimulation made a different in brain activation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
